description.narrative: The UAFC Joint Programme is a consortium and managed by means of the governance and contract management component. There is an independent coordinator for the day to day managment of the partners. Oxfam Novib is responsible for the contract management which implies that Oxfam holds the contracts with the back donors of the consoritum as ell as the contracts with most of the partners. Oxfam is accountable to the donors, the partners report to Oxfam, where consolidation of all the narrative and financial reports takes place, Oxfam also facilitates the audit process.

participating-org.narrative: Youth in Difficult Circumstances is a project implemented in 3 countries: Pakistan, Zimbabwe and South Africa. It is funded by the Dutch Ministry of Foreign Affairs for the period of 2014-2017 and managed by Oxfam Novib The Hague
